Let  

\[
F(x_0,t)\;=\;
\varepsilon(x_0,t)\,
\frac{\displaystyle\Delta\,e^{\varepsilon(x_0,t)\Delta}\mu_t}
     {\displaystyle e^{\varepsilon(x_0,t)\Delta}\mu_t}
\bigl(\Phi_t(x_0)\bigr).
\]

---

### Series form under the scaling assumption  
Using \(e^{\varepsilon\Delta}=\sum_{m\ge0}\frac{\varepsilon^m}{m!}\Delta^m\) and  
\(\Delta^{k}\mu_t=\Theta\!\bigl(e^{\,2k\lambda_1(x_0,t)+\Lambda(x_0,t)t}\bigr)\),

* **Denominator**

\[
e^{\varepsilon\Delta}\mu_t
=\sum_{m\ge0}\frac{\varepsilon^m}{m!}\Delta^{m}\mu_t
=\Theta\!\Bigl(
e^{\Lambda t}
+\varepsilon\,e^{2\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\varepsilon^{2}e^{4\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\dots
\Bigr).
\]

* **Numerator (before the leading \(\varepsilon\))**

\[
\Delta\,e^{\varepsilon\Delta}\mu_t
=\sum_{m\ge0}\frac{\varepsilon^m}{m!}\Delta^{m+1}\mu_t
=\Theta\!\Bigl(
e^{2\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\varepsilon\,e^{4\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\varepsilon^{2}e^{6\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\dots
\Bigr).
\]

* **Numerator with the extra \(\varepsilon\)**

\[
\varepsilon\,\Delta e^{\varepsilon\Delta}\mu_t
=\Theta\!\Bigl(
\varepsilon\,e^{2\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\varepsilon^{2}e^{4\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\varepsilon^{3}e^{6\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\dots
\Bigr).
\]

---

### Big-Θ expression for the fraction  

\[
F(x_0,t)
=\frac{\Theta\!\bigl(
\varepsilon\,e^{2\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\varepsilon^{2}e^{4\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\varepsilon^{3}e^{6\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\dots\bigr)}
{\Theta\!\bigl(
e^{\Lambda t}
+\varepsilon\,e^{2\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\varepsilon^{2}e^{4\lambda_1+\Lambda t}
+\dots\bigr)}.
\]

Factoring \(e^{\Lambda t}\) from numerator and denominator gives the cleaner form

\[
F(x_0,t)
=\frac{\Theta\!\bigl(
\varepsilon\,e^{2\lambda_1}
+\varepsilon^{2}e^{4\lambda_1}
+\varepsilon^{3}e^{6\lambda_1}
+\dots\bigr)}
{\Theta\!\bigl(
1+\varepsilon\,e^{2\lambda_1}
+\varepsilon^{2}e^{4\lambda_1}
+\dots\bigr)},
\]

where every appearance of \(\lambda_1\) and \(\varepsilon\) still carries its \((x_0,t)\) dependence implicitly.
